Files:

costs.txt – Randomly generated cost matrix used for the network topology. All values are ≤ 1000 since the program defines 1000 as infinity (no direct link between routers).

machines.txt – Contains the configuration of the four routers (name, IP address, and port).

ls_router.c – Main program implementing the Link-State routing simulation and Dijkstra’s shortest path algorithm.

ss1.png – Screenshot of the first run showing all four routers running simultaneously with no link cost changes. The routers compute and display their initial least-cost distances.

ss2.png – Screenshot of the second run where Router 1 changes the cost of the link to Router 3. The update is propagated to the other routers and the shortest paths are recomputed.

Used AI to help with approach or errors, did not copy code.
